Order By Clause
The ORDER BY clause in SQL is used to sort the result set of a query by one or more columns, either in ascending (ASC) or descending (DESC) order.
select * from employees

Q1.Write a Query to sort Employees table by salary?
select * from Employees order by Salary

Q2.Write a Query to sort Employees table by salary in Descending order?
select * from Employees order by Salary desc

Q3.Write SQL Query to sort Firstname in ascending order and Salary in Descending order.
select * from Employees order by FirstName asc,Salary desc 


Q4.Write SQL Query to sort Department in ascending order and Salary in Descending order.
select * from Employees order by Department asc,Salary desc 
